# Layout Adjustment Plan

## Goal
Rearrange the elements on the first page (Dashboard) so that the **Character** is positioned between the **Title** and the **Speech Bubble**.

## Proposed Changes

### UI Logic
The user requested the character to be between the speech bubble and the title.
Currently, the visual order is **Speech Bubble -> Character -> Title**.
To satisfy the request in a way that likely improves the layout (Title at the top):
We will change the order to: **Title -> Character -> Speech Bubble**.

### Components

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/Dashboard.jsx)
- Move the `<h1 className="app-title">` element to be the **first child** of `<header className="header">`, placing it before the `.mascot-container`.

#### [MODIFY] [App.css](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.css)
- Update `.speech-bubble` styles to position it **below** the mascot.
  - Currently it is absolute positioned at the top (`top: -10px`).
  - Change to standard static positioning (flex item) or absolute at bottom.
  - Recommended: Switch to flex flow within `.mascot-container` (Mascot First, Bubble Second) and remove absolute positioning for a more natural flow.
  
